Consider the following code snippet regarding C++ tokens and operators. What is the output?
```cpp
int x = 10, y = 20;
if (x++ > 10 && ++y > 20) {
    cout << "True ";
} else {
    cout << "False ";
}
cout << x << " " << y;
```

Analyze the loop behavior in the following snippet using C++ implicit type conversion rules:
```cpp
unsigned int i = 10;
while (i >= 0) {
    if (i == 0) { cout << i; break; }
    cout << i << " ";
    i--;
}
```

